an help you process your feelings and work through the issues that are causing you pain. It is also important to set boundaries with the people in your life who are causing you harm and to prioritize your own well-being. You deserve to be treated with respect and kindness, and it is okay to say no to people who are not treating you well. Remember that you are worthy of love and respect, and that you have the power to create the life you want for yourself. You are not alone, and there is hope for a brighter future. Best of luck to you!'),('Q_015','M0','These. symptoms are all classic to the diagnosis of depression.A diagnosis itself doesn\'t help anyone get better. Â Often people say the word \"depression\" as though it means something terrible. Â  The diagnosis of depression can be depressing.Forget matching symptoms with a diagnosis.More important to improvement is to know the reason for your sadness. Â When people become sad there is a reason for it and knowing this reason is the first step to changing the situation which creates the sadness in you.Think of depression as a way to slow down and examine aspects of your life and relationships. Â If you continue at the same pace of living and didn\'t stop and examine your life, then you may not notice what needs changing.'),('Q_015','M2',' Hello. You are describing symptoms that appear to be consistent with depression. I recommend scheduling a meeting with your primary care physician to obtain a formal assessment and diagnosis. There is no shame in asking for help when you are struggling. A counselor or therapist can help you to develop healthier coping mechanisms, as well as recommend additional resources.'),('Q_015','M3',' It sounds like you may be experiencing symptoms of depression.Ã‚Â Depression is a serious mental illness that affects millions of people each year.Ã‚Â Some signs of depression include:Ã‚Â sadness, loss of interest in activities you used to enjoy, changes in appetite or sleep, feelings of worthlessness or guilt, difficulty concentrating, and thoughts of self-harm or suicide.Ã‚Â If you are experiencing any of these symptoms, it is important to see a mental health professional who can help you get the treatment you need.'),('Q_015','M4','I would recommend that you seek out a therapist who specializes in working with clients who have depression. A therapist can help you to identify the symptoms of depression and help you to develop a treatment plan. A treatment plan is a personalized plan that is developed to help you to achieve your goals. The therapist can help you to identify your goals and help you to achieve them. A therapist can also help you to develop coping skills to help you to manage your symptoms. A therapist can also help you to develop a treatment plan that will help you to achieve your goals. A therapist can also help you to develop a'),('Q_015','M5','I\'m sorry to hear that you are feeling sad. Depression is a serious condition that can have a negative impact on your life. If you are experiencing these symptoms, I would encourage you to seek help from a mental health professional. They can help you to identify the root cause of your depression and develop a treatment plan that is tailored to your specific needs. Remember, you are not alone and there is help available. You deserve to feel happy and fulfilled in your life. Best of luck to you!'),('Q_016','M0','Have you tried to allow yourself some breathing space to emotionally recuperate from the breakup?Sometimes people expect themselves to bounce back faster than is feasible. Â Then, the suffer from both the sadness and distractibility from the breakup in addition to the suffering which is self-induced by not permitting time to feel upset about the loss of the relationship.Be gentle and kind toward yourself because loving yourself will release some of the tension you feel.Since you write that you cannot function and you wrote a question on an online website, maybe you\'re not giving yourself enough credit for your capacity to function.Anyone who is not functioning wouldn\'t be capable to write a question about themselves.While what you write about yourself is in broad terms, my equally broad answer is you may be doing better than you think and the key problem is the discomfort and impatience that the feeling of sadness from the breakup, was more in the past than currently is the case.'),('Q_016','M2',' What are you most worried about?'),('Q_016','M3',' I am sorry you are struggling. Ã‚Â Depression is an awful feeling and I hope we can find some strategies together that could help ease your suffering.Is there anything at all that brings you joy? Ã‚Â It can be anything at all, big or small. Ã‚Â Having some small pleasures in life can help balance out the negative feelings. Ã‚Â Can you think of anything?'),('Q_016','M4','I\'m sorry to hear about your situation. I would recommend that you seek out a therapist who specializes in anxiety and depression. You can also try to find a support group in your area. It\'s always good to have a group of people who are going through the same thing as you. You can also try to find a therapist who specializes in mindfulness. Mindfulness is a great way to help you cope with stress and anxiety. If you have any questions or concerns, please feel free to ask. I wish you the best of luck. Mental health is so important. It\'s great that you are reaching out for help. Take care. Best of luck. Mirella~Image and Likeness Counseling, LLCwww. MirellaImageandLikeness. comwww. Facebook. com/MirellaImageandLikenesswww. Twitter. Pinterest. com/MirellaImageandLikeness/www. Instagram. Flickr. com/photographer/10299577/www. Flick'),('Q_016','M5','I\'m sorry to hear that you are going through this. Depression is a serious condition and it is important to seek help. There are many different types of therapy that can help with depression. One type of therapy that can be helpful is called Cognitive Behavioral Therapy (CBT). CBT helps people to identify negative thought patterns and replace them with more positive and realistic thoughts. Another type of therapy that can be helpful is called Dialectical Behavioral Therapy (DBT). DBT helps people to learn skills to manage their emotions and improve their relationships. There are also medications that can be prescribed to help with depression. It is important to talk to your doctor about what type of treatment would be best for you. I hope that you are able to find some relief soon.'),('Q_017','M0','Depression isn\'t something someone \"has\", it is a dark mood and lack of satisfaction with the way the current life is structured.If you think of depression as motivation to look for new ways to understand yourself, find ways which are more satisfying in your work and relationships, then depression is a charm.The typical attitude most people have when they think of the word \"depression\", is that their life will collapse and decline, they\'ll need to take drugs, and feel hopeless.If you take a different approach and work with your depression as a signal to change some major area or one or two minor areas, then you will engage yourself in creating a better life for yourself!'),('Q_017','M2',' It\'s actually really great that you are aware of changes in your life that are impacting your everyday life, such as stopping caring about your work and feeling like life is pointless. If you\'re considering that you might have depression, you should get some help as soon as possible. I would recommend reaching out to a mental health professional in your area. Depression can be treated and managed.'),('Q_017','M3',' The symptoms of depression do not always include sadness. In fact, many people with depression experience anhedonia, which is the inability to experience pleasure or joy. Depression can also affect sleep, appetite, energy level, and concentration. Additionally, people with depression may feel hopeless, worthless, and like life is not worth living.If you are experiencing a combination of the symptoms listed above, it\'s a good idea to talk to a mental health professional to get a diagnosis and develop a treatment plan.'),('Q_017','M4','I would recommend that you see a therapist. You can discuss your feelings and thoughts with a therapist and they can help you figure out what is going on. It is also important to note that depression is not always sadness. Depression can manifest itself in many different ways. It is important to discuss this with a therapist. I hope this was of some help. Best of luck. Mirella~Image and Likeness Counseling www. imageandlikeness. com\n\nMirella~Image and Likeness Counseling www. com'),('Q_017','M5','Depression is a serious condition that can be debilitating. It is important to seek help from a mental health professional. A therapist can help you to understand your symptoms and develop a treatment plan that is right for you. There are many different types of therapy that can be helpful for depression, including cognitive behavioral therapy, interpersonal therapy, and mindfulness-based therapy. It is important to find a therapist that you feel comfortable with and that you can trust to help you through this difficult time. Remember, you are not alone and there is help available. You deserve to feel better and there is hope for recovery. Reach out for help today. You are not alone. You are not hopeless. You are worthy of happiness and healing. You can get through this. You'),('Q_018','M0','I am so very sorry for how pressured and sad you feel right now.Definitely all family members have an effect on the other ones.From what you write, your family members are not considering the effect their negative comments have on you.Also, keep in mind that each person is responsible for deciding to argue or find a different way to discuss a problem. You are not in control of the other people in your family.More likely they take the easy way out and blame you for what they don\'t want to know about themselves.S